    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>These slightly curved swords measure just over 3 feet in length.</em></p>\n<p>An <em>dueling sword</em> can be used as a martial weapon (in which case it functions as a @Compendium[pf1.weapons-and-ammo.zWRlna42PMJVX6un]{longsword}), but if you have the feat @Compendium[pf1.feats.BJBC4lbo7xGWPsKJ]{Exotic Weapon Proficiency (dueling sword)}, you can use the @Compendium[pf1.feats.vWiTqHC4Y3Xn1Pme]{Weapon Finesse} feat to apply your <em>Dexterity</em> modifier instead of your <em>Strength</em> modifier to <em>attack rolls</em> with a <em>dueling sword</em> sized for you, even though it isn't a light weapon. You can also wield a <em>dueling sword</em> in two hands to apply 1-1/2 times your <em>Strength</em> bonus to damage rolls.</p>"
